    "On the OH-covered silica surface, water molecules exhibit a pronounced tendency to align along the surface normal, with a normalized probability 𝑓 [𝜃 𝑎,𝜃 𝑏 ] = 40.30% in the 0°-30° and 135°-180° ranges, compared to 34.72% for the CH3-covered surface -a relative increase of 16.1%.",
